spanGrp.span: In the old days when we grew up
siid geasiid aa miqoan miqwanyasaneeny qoa geaquus gaguur
And if a person came, if you meet you at home, they had to call you
na mtu wa watu akija hata kukuta nyumbani ni mpaka akuite
aa guu nyas iit ab how ba mooheedan
And you will hear them outside
as ha qamn ng'asheeg gik ba qay ba ikaas qay sinyaagdiin
Now those things of the old days that we experiences
sasa hivi yale mambo yetu zamani tulioyakuta
qadaay ng'anyiid qoot aam guuy buneed
I see that the land, people have been mixed up
There isn't anything any more, it has been lost
roat ng'asheeg gikaany hay ng'asheeg ga
Those things, when they were lost, even things of
mambo yale yalipokuwa yamepotea hata mambo ya
Family relationships, they have been put aside, people have mixed
nya siid geey uundugu aa siid gwasiin gid gasaaj aa sidaany
Often they say "relative" but they do what they want with their person
huwa wanasema ni ndugu lakini wanafanya yale wanayoyataka na mtu wake
ases qay ar aqwaayg badawuuk gekwali
In the old days we would even wear animal skins on our backs
sisi zamani hata ngozi ya mgongoni tunayavaa
ha qamn aa madgwand hud qay gokwalaaj hang'd aqalealea
Now it isn't around any more, and in the old days girls would wear the same clothes
kwa hiyo sasa hivi hakuna tena na zamani binti anavaaga nguo moja
aan ha damdaaw heeshim qoon gwandaaw mambaleawaajandaany aa hang'daany b abadaayd iit ni ba gishiidajeegan mandan
And they would be respectful of their father, and they will have their kanga and shuka, and this news of skirts, there wasn't any of that
na mwenye heshima na baba yake natakuwa na kanga na shuka lake la mgongoni na hizo habari za maasketi ilikuwa hakuna
The skirts in the old days were just for the women
asketi zamani ni kwa akina mama tu
qamn ha buuneed aa manaal ajiinoochanda manaal huuda
Now you won't be able to recognize who is a woman and who is a girl
kwa hiyo saa hivi hutaweza kutambua mama na binti
aa madgwand duung'weend buneed gokwaal gishiid sean
And there are no more animal skins, they are all wearing skirts
na hakuna tena ngozi watu wamevaa asketi wote
ha gijaak geeyeenyi qamn aseasea gid qoawuundaayd migosaayingw
Now what will we say, because of how it has come, won't it be like this?
sasa sisis tutasemaji kwa jinsi ilivyokuja si itakuwa imeshakuwa hivyo
aa gwach ab ha fuuqareed gwach hiit gwach iisuung'uul
And truly we would look at it thoughtfully
na kwa kweli tungeangalia kwa akili nzuri
ab aseasea qamn hij qamuunyiit aa saw gway qwahiit aa aseasea geabariiny hosh qay siilabuun
For us we see it's become a bad time, but they think it is good, but we like the time we have come from
kwa sisi tunaona hapo pamekuwa pabaya lakini wao wanaona ni pazuri ila sisi tunapenda huko tulikotoka
ab gidaab aweachaanj osh gwand ar saygweed
Because in the old days we even had age sets
kwa sababu huko zamani kuna hata rika
qamn deebuug aa madqwanaal -qoon aa madqwanaal qamaat
Now children don't know their father or their mother
sasa hivi watoto hawamjui baba yao wala mama
Now you'd say it's a good time?
